1.title: Lola, Sandy & Moogi
1.plot: The Supervet returns for a new run, this time helping a giant Newfoundland puppy called Lola and a golden Labrador in need of a bionic solution for a deformed front paw.

2.title: Simba, Cato & Tynee
2.plot: A Persian cat has been hit by a car, requiring complex treatment involving a skin graft and putting its crushed bones back together. A rescue dog has a tumour in his jaw removed, and a young staffie-cross has a developmental elbow disease.

3.title: Albie, Flora, and Parker
3.plot: A puppy called Albie has a broken back from being knocked over by a car and needs a complex operation. And a Scottish terrier has a mysterious ailment never seen before.

4.title: Dave & Hermes
4.plot: Noel faces one of his greatest ever practical and ethical challenges as he seeks to provide Hermes, the one-legged tortoise, with three new prosthetic feet. Dave the Rottweiler needs replacement hip replacements.

5.title: Simba, Poppy & Tulee
5.plot: A small Cavachon has been hit by a car but not only has a broken leg but also a serious heart condition. A Labrador needs help with badly formed hips. And a nervous basset hound has a spinal problem.

6.title: Iver, Luca & Bow
6.plot: Professor Noel offers cutting-edge treatment for Luca, a four-year-old springer spaniel with a painful elbow. There's also a leaky Labrador puppy in need of surgery.

7.title: Tom, Otis & Bailey
7.plot: A four-year-old French bulldog suffers a spinal injury being chased by another dog in the park. A rescue Labrador has a wounded paw. And a cocker spaniel has a painful hind leg.

8.title: The Supervet at Christmas 2018
8.plot: It's Christmas at Fitzpatrick Referrals and Professor Noel musters all his skills to treat three very special patients, a rescue puppy, a Dalmation, and a Labrador from Switzerland.

1.title: Scooby, Tiger and Otis
1.plot: David and Gill and their son Freddie are hoping Noel can help their Labrador, Scooby, who has a life-threatening tumour in his leg.

2.title: Rufus, Dixie and Daphne
2.plot: Noel operates on a five-month-old rabbit called Rufus with a badly broken hind leg.

3.title: Jasper, Mojo and Lolli
3.plot: A Staffie puppy called Jasper has a problem with his legs where they are growing in the wrong direction and out of shape. Noel must operate on him soon if they're to have any chance of correcting the problem.

4.title: Pixie and Ellie
4.plot: Owner Diane brings in her 12-year-old cat Pixie, who's been hit by a car. Noel believes he can help Pixie walk again by giving her a revolutionary bionic implant.

10.title: Whatever It Takes
10.plot: Professor Noel Fitzpatrick tries to save the leg of a Cockapoo hit by a lawn mower to give her a future running around with all four limbs.

imdb.plot outline: This program follows a veterinarian in England who treats animals with severe and/or life-threatening injuries. He has a state of the art veterinary facility,but he also uses procedures that he has invented to care for the animals who come in. He has an excellent bed side manner for his 4 legged patients and their 2 legged "parents".
imdb.title: The Supervet
plot: Behind-the-scenes series following the staff at Fitzpatrick Referrals veterinary practice as they employ cutting edge technology to treat their sick and injured patients.::Anonymous

This program follows a veterinarian in England who treats animals with severe and/or life-threatening injuries. He has a state of the art veterinary facility,but he also uses procedures that he has invented to care for the animals who come in. He has an excellent bed side manner for his 4 legged patients and their 2 legged "parents".::Kay Weir
